for&nbsp;we&nbsp;wouldn’t&nbsp;know&nbsp;what&nbsp;to&nbsp;buy!

00:01:47.502 --> 00:01:50.251
So&nbsp;we&nbsp;are&nbsp;here&nbsp;just&nbsp;to&nbsp;say&nbsp;thanks.

00:01:50.886 --> 00:01:55.668
Thanks&nbsp;for&nbsp;changing&nbsp;the&nbsp;lives&nbsp;of&nbsp;millions
of&nbsp;children&nbsp;(and&nbsp;adults!)&nbsp;around&nbsp;the&nbsp;world,

00:01:55.668 --> 00:01:59.982
showing&nbsp;them&nbsp;the&nbsp;pleasure&nbsp;of&nbsp;reading
and stimulating&nbsp;our&nbsp;creativity,

00:02:00.216 --> 00:02:02.934
writing&nbsp;books&nbsp;that&nbsp;not&nbsp;only&nbsp;entertained&nbsp;us,

00:02:02.934 --> 00:02:06.422
but&nbsp;also&nbsp;helped&nbsp;us&nbsp;in&nbsp;several
difficult&nbsp;moments&nbsp;of&nbsp;our&nbsp;lives,

00:02:06.731 --> 00:02:08.781
showed&nbsp;us&nbsp;a&nbsp;light&nbsp;at&nbsp;the&nbsp;end&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;tunnel,

00:02:08.781 --> 00:02:12.237
for&nbsp;“happiness&nbsp;can&nbsp;be&nbsp;found
even&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;darkest&nbsp;of&nbsp;times,

00:02:12.237 --> 00:02:14.699
if&nbsp;one&nbsp;only&nbsp;remembers&nbsp;to&nbsp;turn&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp; light.”

00:02:14.858 --> 00:02:19.264
Thank&nbsp;you,&nbsp;Jo,&nbsp;for&nbsp;shining&nbsp;a&nbsp;light
on&nbsp;the&nbsp;life of&nbsp;thousand&nbsp;of&nbsp;children

00:02:19.264 --> 00:02:23.690
who&nbsp;live&nbsp;in&nbsp;institutes&nbsp;all&nbsp;over&nbsp;the&nbsp;world,&nbsp;giving
them&nbsp;back&nbsp;their&nbsp;right&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;life&nbsp;amongst&nbsp;family.

00:02:23.690 --> 00:02:26.566
Thank&nbsp;you&nbsp;for&nbsp;allowing&nbsp;us
to&nbsp;meet&nbsp;incredible people

00:02:26.566 --> 00:02:29.925
from&nbsp;all&nbsp;around&nbsp;the&nbsp;country
–&nbsp;and&nbsp;even&nbsp;the&nbsp;world,

00:02:29.925 --> 00:02:33.656
for&nbsp;“though&nbsp;we&nbsp;may&nbsp;come&nbsp;from&nbsp;different
places,&nbsp;and&nbsp;speak&nbsp;in&nbsp;different&nbsp;tongues,

00:02:33.656 --> 00:02:35.905
our&nbsp;hearts&nbsp;beat&nbsp;as&nbsp;one.”

00:02:36.370 --> 00:02:38.585
Oh,&nbsp;and&nbsp;thank&nbsp;you so
much&nbsp;for&nbsp;reminding&nbsp;us&nbsp;that

00:02:38.585 --> 00:02:44.464
“if&nbsp;Harry&nbsp;Potter&nbsp;taught&nbsp;us&nbsp;anything,
it’s&nbsp;that&nbsp;no&nbsp;one&nbsp;should&nbsp;live&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;closet”!

00:02:44.949 --> 00:02:48.244
For&nbsp;the&nbsp;laughter,&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;tears,&nbsp;for
the anticipation&nbsp;of&nbsp;every&nbsp;launch,

00:02:48.244 --> 00:02:52.479
and&nbsp;now&nbsp;with&nbsp;“Fantastic&nbsp;Beasts”
and the&nbsp;Cormoran&nbsp;Strike&nbsp;novels.

00:02:52.792 --> 00:02:55.311
Do&nbsp;you&nbsp;have&nbsp;any&nbsp;idea
